                            <comment id="14072486" author="marmbrus" created="Wed, 23 Jul 2014 22:44:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kayousterhout&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kayousterhout&quot;&gt;kayousterhout&lt;/a&gt; reports this is fixed in master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14072525" author="kayousterhout" created="Wed, 23 Jul 2014 23:13:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=marmbrus&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;marmbrus&quot;&gt;marmbrus&lt;/a&gt; Sorry I spoke too soon &amp;#8211; this is still broken but much less broken than before.  By default, SparkContext.clean() now checks if tasks are serializable, which typically prevents this problem because the stage never gets submitted.  However, checking if tasks are serializable can be disabled (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/143&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/143&lt;/a&gt;), in which case you can still see this problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
